Looking at the code, I need to analyze the `findWrapPos` method and understand which test cases actually expose the bug.

Let me trace through the buggy code:

```java
protected int findWrapPos(String text, int width, int startPos)
{
    int pos;

    // the line ends before the max wrap pos or a new line char found
    if (((pos = text.indexOf('\n', startPos)) != -1 && pos <= width)
            || ((pos = text.indexOf('\t', startPos)) != -1 && pos <= width))
    {
        return pos + 1;
    }
    else if (startPos + width >= text.length())
    {
        return -1;
    }

    // look for the last whitespace character before startPos+width
    pos = startPos + width;

    char c;

    while ((pos >= startPos) && ((c = text.charAt(pos)) != ' ')
            && (c != '\n') && (c != '\r'))
    {
        --pos;
    }

    // if we found it - just return
    if (pos > startPos)
    {
        return pos;
    }

    // if we didn't find one, simply chop at startPos+width
    pos = startPos + width;
    while ((pos <= text.length()) && ((c = text.charAt(pos)) != ' ')
           && (c != '\n') && (c != '\r'))
    {
        ++pos;
    }        
    return pos == text.length() ? -1 : pos;
}
```

The bug is in the first condition: `pos <= width` should be `pos <= startPos + width`. The method is checking if the newline/tab position is within the allowed width from position 0, but it should check if it's within the width from `startPos`.

Also, in the last while loop, `pos <= text.length()` will cause an `IndexOutOfBoundsException` when `pos == text.length()` because `text.charAt(pos)` would be out of bounds. It should be `pos < text.length()`.

Looking at the test cases, `testFindWrapPos` directly tests this method and would expose both bugs. The test case at line "assertEquals("wrap position 2", -1, hf.findWrapPos(text, 8, 8));" would fail with the first bug, and other scenarios might trigger the IndexOutOfBoundsException.

Other test methods that call `printHelp` or text rendering methods would indirectly use `findWrapPos`, potentially triggering the bug with certain text patterns.

